Key Match Events: India won by 68 runs against England in the T20 World Cup 2024 semi-final.
Rohit Sharma scored 57 runs off 39 balls.
Chris Jordan took 3 wickets for 37 runs.
Kuldeep Yadav and Axar Patel each took 3 wickets, with figures of 3-19 and 3-23 respectively.
Axar Patel dismissed Jos Buttler, Jonny Bairstow, and Moeen Ali.
Kuldeep Yadav dismissed Sam Curran and Harry Brook.
Liam Livingstone was run-out after a mix-up.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on a slow and low-bounce pitch in Providence, Guyana.
India's spinners played a crucial role in their victory.
Rain interrupted the game, consuming 153 minutes of playtime.
